1. e4 e5 2. f4 exf4 3. Nf3 Ne7 4. d4 d5 5. Bd3 $5 dxe4 6. Bxe4 Ng6 $1 7. Qe2
Be7 8. h4 (8. Nc3 {We can't predict every move but based on our ideas we know
that Black is doing very well here because these are not the best moves for
White.} O-O 9. Bd2 Nd7 10. O-O-O Nf6 $17) 8... O-O $5 {the safe choice} (8...
Nxh4 $5 {A risky choice but playable.} 9. Nc3 (9. Nxh4 $2 Bxh4+ 10. Kf1 Kf8 $5
11. Bxf4 Bg5 12. Bg3 Qf6+ 13. Kg1 Nc6 $1 14. c3 Bf5 $17) 9... Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3
Qxd4 11. Bxf4 c6 12. Rd1 Qf6 $17) 9. h5 Nh4 10. Bxf4 Nxf3+ 11. Qxf3 Qxd4 $5 (
11... Nd7 $5 {This is the move we play. Check the theoretical file.}) 12. Nc3
