1. e4 e5 2. f4 d5 $5 {My second suggestion. This following line hasn't been
played that much and so far most of the games that have been weren't so great.}
(2... exf4 3. Nf3 d5 4. exd5 Be7 {Transposes.}) 3. exd5 exf4 4. Nf3 Be7 $5 {
[%cal Ye7h4] A very rare line that is also very good for Black, and so far it
hasn't been played in the right way. This time for a change it is Black who is
willing to sacrifice a pawn for the initiative.} 5. Bc4 (5. d4 Bh4+ 6. Ke2 Bg4
7. Bxf4 Qxd5 $17) (5. Bb5+ $5 c6 6. dxc6 Nxc6 $3 {A very simple move that
hasn't been played much. White can't caste because of Qb6 and in general Black
has a very good play.} 7. d4 Bh4+ 8. Kf1 (8. g3 $2 fxg3 9. O-O Bh3 (9... gxh2+
$5) 10. Re1+ Kf8 $17) 8... Be7 $1 (8... Bg4 $1 9. Bxf4 (9. d5 $2 Qb6 10. Qe2+
Kf8 11. dxc6 Re8 $19) 9... Nge7 $15) 9. d5 Nf6 10. Nc3 a6 11. Ba4 b5 12. Bb3
Na5 $132) 5... Bh4+ $1 6. Kf1 (6. g3 $2 {too naive to be good!} fxg3 7. Qe2+ (
7. O-O gxh2+ 8. Kh1 Bh3 $17 (8... Be7 $1 9. d4 Nf6 $15) 9. Nxh4 Qxh4 10. Re1+
$4 Ne7 11. Nc3 Qg3 12. Qe2 Bg2+ $19) 7... Kf8 $1 8. O-O Bh3 9. Re1 Nd7 $17 10.
Nc3 Bg4 $17) 6... Be7 $1 (6... Bf6 7. Nc3 Ne7 8. d4 Nd7 9. Bxf4 Nb6 $44 {
[%cal Ye8g8]}) 7. d4 Nf6 8. Nc3 (8. Bxf4 Nxd5 9. Bxd5 Qxd5 10. Bxc7 Qc4+ 11.
Kf2 Qxc7 $19) 8... Nbd7 $1 {we want a fast Nbd7-Nb6 !!} 9. Bxf4 Nb6 10. Qe2 (
10. Bb3 $6 Nbxd5 11. Nxd5 Nxd5 12. Bxd5 Qxd5 13. Qe2 Be6 $17) (10. Bb5+ $6 Bd7
11. Bxd7+ Qxd7 12. Ne5 Qd8 13. Kf2 O-O 14. Rf1 Nbxd5 $17) 10... O-O 11. Bb3 a5
$1 12. a3 c5 $3 13. dxc6 (13. dxc5 Bxc5 14. Rd1 Re8 15. Qb5 Bd6 $17 16. Bg5 Bd7
17. Qd3 a4 18. Ba2 h6 19. Bh4 Bg4 20. h3 Bh5 $17 {In this open position it is
almost impossible for white to restore coordination.} 21. Qd4 Nbd7 $17) 13...
bxc6 $15 {[%cal Yc8a6]} 0-1

