{[%evp 0,28,16,28,38,32,32,-12,-11,-11,3,-6,-16,-40,-63,-35,-28,-96,-78,-78,
-58,-116,-104,-144,-137,-134,-127,-143,-134,-138,-114]} 1. e4 e5 2. d4 {
This system is used mainly for surprise. However, if we want to play 1...e5,
we must know all these little systems very well.} exd4 3. Qxd4 Nc6 4. Qe3 (4.
Qd3 {Tricky move. White is hoping for Nf6 where he can follow up with Nc3 and
later on Bf4 and 0-0-0 ideas.} d5 $3 $13 5. exd5 Nb4 6. Qb3 (6. Qe4+ Qe7 $17) (
6. Qe2+ Qe7 7. Be3 Nxd5 $17) 6... Qxd5 7. Qxd5 Nxd5 $15 {[%cal Yd5b4] In such
symmetrical positions development is very important. Here Black is clearly
ahead which leads to a better position.}) (4. Qc4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 $1 $132 {
check the model games.} 6. Bd2 O-O 7. O-O-O d6 {I would say this is the best
move here.} (7... a5 $1 8. f3 Ne5 9. Qe2 Re8 $36) 8. f3 a5 $3 $36 {The idea is
to have the bishop on b4 protected so we can play Ne5 and in the future we
will go for a4-a3 idea.}) 4... Nf6 5. Nc3 (5. Bd2 Be7 $1 6. Nc3 (6. c4 O-O 7.
Nc3 Re8 8. O-O-O Bb4 9. f3 d6 $15 10. g4 Be6 11. g5 Nd7 $17) 6... d5 7. exd5
Nxd5 8. Nxd5 Qxd5 9. Ne2 Bf5 $1 $15 10. Nc3 Qe6 11. O-O-O O-O-O $15) 5... Bb4 {
The same position with the queen on d3 would have been good for White but he
can't get it! (3.Qxd4 Nc6 4.Qd3 d5! =+)} 6. Bd2 O-O 7. O-O-O Re8 {Black has a
nice play when he reaches this position.} 8. Qg3 (8. Bc4 d6 9. f3 (9. Nf3 Be6
10. Bxe6 Rxe6 $36 11. Ng5 Re8 12. f3 Ne5 $15) 9... Ne5 10. Bb3 a5 $17 11. a3
Bc5 12. Qe1 b5 $17) (8. Qf4 $5 Ne5 $3 9. f3 (9. Nf3 Ng6 10. Qe3 Bxc3 11. Bxc3
Nxe4 $17) 9... c6 $3 10. Nge2 (10. g4 d5 11. g5 Ng6 12. Qg3 Nh5 13. Qf2 Bxc3
14. Bxc3 Qxg5+ $17) 10... Bf8 11. Nd4 b5 $36) (8. f3 d5 $15 9. Qf2 dxe4 10. Bg5
Bd7 11. Nd5 e3 $3 $19 12. Nxe3 (12. Qh4 Bd2+ 13. Kb1 Bf5 14. Nxf6+ gxf6 15.
Bxf6 Qd6 $1 $19) 12... Bc5 $19) 8... Nxe4 9. Nxe4 Rxe4 10. Bxb4 (10. c3 Be7 $1
11. f4 (11. Bd3 Bh4 12. Qf3 Ra4 $3 {Our rook stands quite well on a4. At some
moment the rook gets back into the game through the fifth rank.} 13. Kb1 Ne5
14. Qe2 Nxd3 15. Qxd3 d6 16. Nf3 Bf6 $19 17. b3 Ra5 $19) 11... d5 12. Bd3 Bf5
$3 13. Nf3 Qd7 14. Bxe4 dxe4 $17 (14... Bxe4 $17) 15. c4 Qe6 16. Bc3 Bg6 17.
Nd4 Nxd4 18. Rxd4 e3 $17) (10. Bf4 Qf6 $3 11. Nh3 (11. Bxc7 d6 $19 {[%csl Yc7]}
) 11... h6 $5 $17 12. Bd3 Re7 $1 13. c3 Bc5 14. Rhe1 d6 $19) 10... Rxb4 11. c3
Ra4 12. Kb1 d6 13. Bd3 (13. f3 Be6 14. b3 Ra5 $19) 13... Rg4 $17 14. Qh3 h6 $19
*

