not the best option because of} 8. d4 Nf5 {We are planning d5 next but
unfortunately its white to move.} 9. d5 $1) 8. Nf3 (8. Nd5 {is not really a
trouble because of} Bd8) 8... c6 9. O-O d5 {These are the typical positions
where only the e-file is open. It can come from many different openings like
Berlin, French exchange, etc. The most important rule to remember is that a
knight on f3 or f6 is a source of concern. And on the other hand, a knight f5
or f4 tends to be very good.} 10. Re1 Na6 11. d4 h5 $1 {Black is playing for a
win because the knight on f5 is better then the knight on f3.} 12. Ne2 (12. Nb1
