-553,-793,-829,-844,-668,-2064,-1800,-1936,-2340]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3
Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. e5 Nd5 6. cxd4 {Previously we saw 6.Bc4} Bb4+ $1 {We aim for
fast development. Here white has to choose between: 7.Nd2 and 7.Bd2} 7. Bd2
Bxd2+ 8. Nbxd2 d6 9. Bc4 Be6 {This is also good enough, but the best move is 9.
.. Nf4} (9... Nf4 $1 $132 {This is very interesting according to the computer.
In fact, black is playing for an advantage because white has overextended in
the center.} 10. O-O O-O 11. Re1 dxe5 12. dxe5 Be6 (12... Bg4 13. Re4) 13. Bxe6
fxe6 $17 {d5,d4 & d3 squares are weak. Black is better.}) 10. Qb3 (10. exd6
Qxd6 11. O-O O-O-O (11... O-O 12. Ne4 Qb4 13. Qc2 h6 14. Rfe1 Nf4 15. Bxe6 fxe6
(15... Nxe6 16. Nf6+ gxf6 17. Rxe6 fxe6 18. Qg6+ Kh8 $11)) 12. Re1 Rhe8 13. Bb5
Nde7) 10... dxe5 11. dxe5 O-O $36 12. Qxb7 $4 {These complications don't work
well for white.} Ndb4 13. Qb5 Rb8 14. Qc5 Nc2+ 15. Ke2 N6d4+ 16. Nxd4 Nxd4+ 17.
Kf1 Rxb2 18. Rd1 Rc2 {Black is completely better because of his active pieces.}
19. Qb4 Nc6 20. Qa4 Bxc4+ 21. Kg1 Rxd2 22. Rc1 Nxe5 23. h4 Qd4 0-1

