1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 Bb7 $5 {a rare but very interesting alternative to the main
line! Generally speaking, Black wants to castle long and attack the pawn on e5
with Re8 and even with f6. Sometimes, we play c6-c5 to open up the bishop.} 10.
Bd2 {The mainline.} (10. h4 {Now there are two good moves for Black:} O-O-O ({
Against h4, generally,} 10... Qe6 {tends to be a good move.} 11. Bd2 (11. b3
O-O-O ({We can even go for short castling.} 11... Bb4 {At least practically,
this move is also quite interesting.} 12. Bb2 O-O {Intending f6 or d6.} 13.
O-O-O a5 {This is an unclear position. Objectively, I have a feeling that
White is somehow better here.}) 12. Bb2 Re8 {We are threatening to win a pawn.}
13. Rh3 {A useful move planning to play Re3.} Qh6 $132 {Preventing him from
castling with nice, unclear play.}) 11... Be7 12. O-O-O O-O 13. Qe4 d5 14. exd6
Qxe4 15. Nxe4 cxd6 16. Bg5 f6 17. Be3 d5 18. Nc5 Bc8 19. cxd5 cxd5 20. Bd3 Bg4
21. f3 Bh5 22. Kb1 Rfc8 {1/2-1/2 Braeuer, F-Votava,J/Germany GER 2023/The Week
in Chess 1478}) 11. Bf4 (11. Bg5 f6 12. exf6 gxf6 13. Qxe7 Bxe7 14. Be3 d5 $132
{We are threatening to take on c4 with the pawn and we have a very good game.})
11... Ba6 $1 12. b3 Qa3 $132 (12... f6 $132)) (10. Bf4 {This move has been
played several times. Black usually castled long intending g5 and Bg7. This is
playable. However, I found an even better idea:} Ba6 $1 {a very nice idea ! ...
we lose a tempo, but provoke b3 while the bishop cannot go to b2 !! ....
details!} (10... O-O-O $5 11. O-O-O g5 $1 12. Bg3 (12. Be3 c5 $132) 12... h5 {
This is also quite good.} 13. h4 g4 $1 $132 {Our bishop will go to h6 or g7
and then we will play f6 or d6. At a good moment, we will play c5.} 14. f4 (14.
Kb1 Kb8 {For example,} 15. f4 gxf3 16. gxf3 Bg7 $132 {With nice, unclear play
and chances for both sides.} 17. f4 f6 18. Bg2 Ba6 ({We may consider} 18... Qb4
{which is very annoying.}) 19. b3 fxe5 20. fxe5 Qb4 21. Qb2 Rhg8 {And nice
play. Of course, it is a very complicated battle. We are always in danger of
not activating the Ba6 and Nb6 in time.}) 14... d5 15. Qc2 Bg7 16. cxd5 cxd5
17. Nb5 Kb8 18. Nd4 Bh6 19. Kb1 c5 20. Nf5 Qc7 21. Nd6 Rxd6 22. exd6 Qxd6 23.
Qc3 d4 24. f5 Be4+ 25. Ka1 Bf4 26. Qe1 Re8 27. Bxf4 Qxf4 28. Bb5 Re5 29. Rf1
Qe3 30. Qa5 f6 31. Rde1 Qg3 32. Qd2 Nc8 33. Bd7 Nb6 34. Be6 Qxh4 35. Qf4 Bxg2
36. Rxe5 fxe5 37. Qxe5+ Kb7 38. Rc1 d3 39. Qxc5 Qd8 40. Bb3 d2 41. Rg1 h4 42.
Qf2 h3 43. Rd1 Qc7 44. Qxd2 Bf3 45. f6 Bxd1 46. f7 Bf3 47. f8=Q h2 48. a4 h1=Q+
49. Ka2 Bd5 50. Qfb4 Qf7 {0-1 Movsesian, S-Sahidi,S/Skalica 2021/CBM 204 Extra}
) 11. b3 {When we play b3 in chess, we usually want to continue with Bb2. But
his bishop is already on f4.} (11. Qe4 {is not working because of} Qb4 {
and we are winning a pawn.} 12. O-O-O Nxc4 13. Bxc4 Qxc4 {Black is better.} 14.
Rd4 Qe6 15. Rhd1 O-O-O 16. Ra4 Bb7 17. Rxa7 Bc5 $15) 11... g5 ({Now even} 11...
Nd5 $5 $132 {is good.}) 12. Bg3 Nd5 $132 {with very nice, unclear play. We may
castle short or long. We have access to the dark squares on the queenside as
the bishop is on g3.}) (10. b3 $6 {Once again, this move is not working.} O-O-O
$15 11. Bb2 Re8 ({According to the computer, even} 11... g6 {is good.} 12.
O-O-O Bg7 13. f4 f6 14. exf6 Qxf6 {There is no good move with the knight and
we are even threatening f4.} 15. g3 Rhe8 16. Qd2 d5 17. Bh3+ Kb8 18. Na4 Qf8
19. c5 Nxa4 20. Bxg7 Qxg7 21. bxa4 Qa1+ 22. Kc2 Qxa2+ 23. Kd3 Qc4# {0-1
Mahitosh,D-Hosseinzadeh,N/Chess.com INT 2022/EXT 2023}) 12. f4 g5 {Also 12...
f6 was good.} 13. Ne4 Bg7 14. Nxg5 f6 15. Nf3 fxe5 16. fxe5 Bh6 {Black is
doing very, very well. White is stuck in the center.} 17. Qd3 Rhg8 18. g3 d5
19. Be2 Rd8 20. c5 Qxc5 21. Nd4 Rdf8 22. Nf5 Bg5 23. h4 Bd8 24. Rf1 Kb8 25. Rc1
