1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 Bb7 10. Bf4 O-O-O ({Don't forget that a very interesting move
here is} 10... Ba6 {to provoke b3.} 11. Qe4 Qb4 12. O-O-O Nxc4 13. Bxc4 Qxc4 {
and we put the queen on e6 if Rd4.}) 11. O-O-O g5 {is playable here and very
good.} 12. Bg3 Bg7 {12...h5 might be a better move here.} 13. h4 h6 14. hxg5
hxg5 15. Rxh8 Rxh8 16. f4 Re8 17. Re1 gxf4 18. Bxf4 Ba6 19. b3 {Now Black is
winning. Remember this tactic to play Ba6 to provoke b3.} Qa3+ 20. Kb1 (20. Qb2
Qxb2+ 21. Kxb2 d6 {Of course, we need to calculate} 22. c5 Bxf1 23. Rxf1 dxc5 {
I am not really impressed by our winning chances but we are a pawn up.}) (20.
Qb2 Qc5 {is maybe better.}) 20... Qa5 ({He could have played} 20... Bxc4) 21.
Qe3 Bxe5 22. Bxe5 f6 23. Kb2 Rxe5 {Now things are very clear.} 24. Qf2 d6 25.
g4 Kb8 26. Rxe5 Qxe5 {The queen is centralized and protecting everything. Now
the game is completely lost.} 27. Qf5 Qd4 28. Qd3 Qxg4 29. Bh3 Qf4 30. a4 Qe5
31. Bg2 Bb7 32. Qe4 a5 33. Qxe5 fxe5 34. Kc2 Nd7 35. Bh3 Nc5 36. Nd1 Bc8 37.
Bg2 Kb7 38. Ne3 Kb6 39. Kc3 Na6 40. Nf1 Bf5 41. Ng3 Bg6 0-1

