1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 Ba6 10. Qe4 {Because c4 is kind of weak.} f6 11. exf6 gxf6 12. b3
(12. Qxe7+ Bxe7 13. b3 d5 14. cxd5 Bxf1 15. Rxf1 cxd5 16. Bb2 c5 17. O-O-O d4
18. Ne4 Nd5 $17) 12... O-O-O 13. Qxe7 Bxe7 {Usually, they would play 14.Bb2
against which we play 14...d5.} 14. Bd2 d5 (14... Bc5 $3 $15 {is even better,
according to my computer. We threaten to take on f2 if White castles. We can
also give a check on e8 followed by d5.}) 15. cxd5 Bxf1 16. Rxf1 cxd5 17. O-O-O
Rhe8 (17... d4 $1 18. Ne4 Nd5 $15 19. Rfe1 Rhg8 20. g3 $4 f5 $19) 18. Rfe1 Kb7
19. Kc2 Bd6 20. Nb5 Bc5 21. Bf4 c6 22. Rxe8 Rxe8 23. Nd6+ Bxd6 24. Bxd6 Nd7 {
Maybe now White is slightly better.} 25. Kd2 {This seems to be a mistake.} c5 {
and the king comes to c6 very fast. Do not forget that Black already has a
passed pawn in this endgame.} 26. Re1 Rxe1 27. Kxe1 Kc6 28. Bf4 d4 29. Kd2 Kd5
{Black has an advantage. With perfect play, this might be a draw. But still,
there is a lot of play.} 30. f3 c4 {Stopping Kd3.} 31. bxc4+ Kxc4 {With
perfect play, this should be a draw.} 32. g4 d3 33. Bd6 Nb6 34. Be7 Nd5 35. Bd8
Kd4 36. h4 Kc4 37. f4 Kd4 38. g5 fxg5 39. fxg5 Ke4 40. h5 Nf4 41. g6 hxg6 42.
h6 g5 43. Bxg5 Ng6 44. Be3 Nh8 45. Bxa7 Nf7 46. Be3 Ne5 47. h7 Nf7 48. a4 Kf5
49. Bd4 Ke4 50. Bc3 Kd5 51. a5 Kc5 52. Kxd3 Kb5 53. Ke4 Ng5+ 54. Kf5 Nxh7 55.
