1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 Bb7 {The most welcomed thing for us here are dubious novelties
by our opponents.} 10. Bd2 O-O-O 11. O-O-O Re8 12. f4 f6 13. exf6 Qf7 ({
We don't want to play an endgame here.} 13... gxf6 $6 14. Qxe7 Bxe7 15. Bd3 {
For example,} c5 {We are not doing well here.} 16. Rhg1 h5 17. g3 Bd8 {This
game is very uncomfortable.} (17... d5 18. cxd5) 18. b3 Rhg8 19. Rde1 {We are
slowly getting outplayed. White is hoping to reach such endgames.}) 14. Qf2
gxf6 {With good play for Black. Now, White went wrong:} 15. Qd4 {We are out of
book.} c5 16. Qd3 f5 {Looks very logical, controlling everything.} 17. Rg1 {
The bishop cannot be developed otherwise.} Bg7 {The bishop clearly belongs
here.} 18. Be3 d6 {Black is doing very well.} 19. Bf2 (19. Be2 {here we can
take} Nxc4) 19... Be4 (19... Ba6 {Maybe he can play 20.Nb5} 20. b3 {This is a
mistake.} Qf6 21. Kc2 Bb7 (21... d5 {This appears to be very good.})) 20. Nxe4
Rxe4 {I think this is very simple and good.} 21. Qa3 (21. b3 {Obviously, the
move is not to take on f4 but to play} Qf6) 21... Rhe8 22. Qxa7 Rxf4 23. Bg3
Rxc4+ 24. Kb1 (24. Bxc4 Qxc4+ 25. Kb1 Re2 {[%csl Rb2] Obviously, this is
checkmate.}) 24... Qf6 25. Qa3 Re3 {Very nice.} 26. Bd3 Rb4 27. Rd2 Na4 {
In the end, everything entered.} 28. Ba6+ Kb8 29. Qxe3 Rxb2+ 30. Kc1 Rxd2 31.
Qe8+ Ka7 32. Kxd2 Qd4+ 33. Bd3 Bh6+ 34. Ke2 Nc3+ 35. Ke1 Qxg1+ 36. Bf1 Qd4 37.
Be2 Be3 0-1

