c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 Bb7 10. Bf4 g6 {Not a good move, according to the computer. When
you play such a move, you have to know it very well because otherwise, you can
lose very badly.} 11. O-O-O Bg7 {But now all of a sudden it gives a good game
for Black} 12. Ne4 (12. h4 {looks interesting because if we castle long he has
Bg5.} O-O 13. h5 Rae8 $132 {There is no attack. If he takes} 14. hxg6 {we take
with the f-pawn} fxg6 {and there are also some weaknesses for White.}) 12...
O-O-O $17 {Black is much better here all of a sudden.} 13. Bg5 Qxe5 14. Bxd8
Rxd8 {The Bg7 is a monster.} 15. Qc2 c5 {With a knight on e4, this move quite
often tends to be good.} 16. Nc3 Nxc4 {A nice little combination grabbing
another pawn.} 17. Bxc4 Qf4+ 18. Kb1 Qxc4 19. f3 Bc6 {Black is better here.}
20. Rhe1 f5 21. Qd3 Qxd3+ 22. Rxd3 c4 23. Rde3 d5 24. Re7 Bf8 25. Rxh7 d4 26.
Nd1 Bb4 27. Re6 Ba4 28. Ra6 Bd7 29. Rxa7 Kb8 30. Ra6 f4 31. Kc1 Bb5 32. Rxg6 d3
33. b3 c3 34. Nxc3 Bxc3 35. Re6 d2+ 36. Kd1 Bd3 0-1

