1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
c4 Nb6 9. Nc3 Bb7 10. Bd2 (10. Bf4 {Here, I found} Ba6 11. b3 Qe6) 10... O-O-O
11. O-O-O Re8 12. Re1 Qb4 {is not really a good move, according to the
computer.} ({Better is} 12... Qe6 {and we develop the pieces, with fine play.}
13. f4 Ba6 {provoking} 14. b3 Ba3+ 15. Kb1 f6 16. exf6 Qf5+ {and the game
continues.}) 13. Kb1 {is not the best, according to the computer.} ({White
should have played the very difficult move} 13. Qd3 {the idea is} Ba6 14. Re4 {
and not to have to play b3.}) 13... Ba6 14. Nd5 {This is just a calculation.}
Qa4 15. Nxb6+ axb6 16. g3 f6 {Typical ideas but with calculation.} 17. f4 fxe5
18. fxe5 Bb4 19. Bh3 Re7 20. b3 Qa5 21. Bxb4 Qxb4 22. Rd1 Rd8 {Black wants to
move his king.} 23. Rhe1 Kb8 {Now he has ideas with d5.} 24. Qb2 Bc8 {
Protecting the pawn to double the rooks.} 25. a3 Qc5 {Here the queen is almost
trapped. But only almost.} 26. Re4 Rf8 27. b4 Qf2 28. Re2 Qf7 29. c5 Qh5 30.
Bg2 Rf2 31. Rde1 Rxe2 32. Qxe2 Qf5+ 33. Ka1 d6 34. cxd6 cxd6 35. Qd2 Qd7 36.
Qf2 Qc7 37. Rc1 (37. exd6 Rxe1+ 38. Qxe1 Qxd6) 37... d5 38. Qf4 Rxe5 {In this
lost position, White lost on time.} 0-1

