f6.}) 13... d5 ({Even} 13... f6 {looks good} 14. Nc5 fxe5 {When you have your
king in the center, tactics will arise. We threaten to take on f4.}) 14. cxd5
Bxf1 15. Kxf1 {He should better take with the king to unpin it.} cxd5 16. Nc5 {
And now we break.} f6)) 10... Ba6 11. Bg5 Qxe5 12. Bf6 {This is totally wrong.}
Nxf6 13. Nxf6+ Bxf6 0-1

