{In this game Black reached comfortable equality ..and right at the moment
when he started taking over in the endgame ..he proposed a draw with 26...a5? .
. ..study what happens after 26...a6!} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4
Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. Bd3 d5 7. exd5 cxd5 8. O-O Be7 {This is already an
improvement because if White goes 9.Nc3, our bishop is on e7.} 9. h3 {This
move is a little bit slow.} O-O {Black is doing very well.} 10. Re1 Be6 11. Nd2
(11. Bf4 {We have many interesting ideas.} c5 {Of course, if he plays} 12. c4 {
in such an open position, we will be more than happy to take this pawn.} ({
Now I like} 12. c3 Bd6 {And if he plays} 13. Bg5 {then there is this
interesting possibility:} h6 14. Bh4 g5 15. Bg3 Bxg3 16. fxg3 {We take
advantage that his rook is not even on the f-line.} Qd6 {We have a perfect
game.}) 12... dxc4 13. Bf1 {It would be naive for White to think that he could
slowly get the pawn back. This is never going to happen. The position is very
open and we have active play with Nd5.}) 11... h6 12. Nf3 c5 13. b3 Ne4 ({
I believe} 13... c4 {is very interesting with strong counterplay.}) 14. Bxe4
dxe4 15. Qxd8 Rfxd8 16. Rxe4 {Strong complications arose after precise
calculations.} Bf6 17. Rb1 Bf5 18. Re2 Rd1+ 19. Re1 Bxc2 20. Rxd1 Bxb1 21. Rd2
Rd8 22. Bb2 Bg5 23. Rxd8+ Bxd8 24. a3 Bc2 25. b4 cxb4 26. axb4 a5 $2 {Black
was happy with a draw and played this unfortunate move.} ({The correct move is,
of course} 26... a6 $1 {We are willing to play such positons for hours.} 27.
Nd4 (27. Ne5 Ba4 28. Nd3 Bb5 29. Nc5 Be7 30. Bd4 h5 31. f3 h4 32. Kf2 f6 (32...
g6) 33. Ke3 Kf7 34. Bc3 a5 35. Kd2 a4 (35... axb4 36. Bxb4 Bf1)) 27... Bd3 28.
Nc6 (28. f3 Bb6 29. Kf2 Kf8 30. Ke3 Bf1 31. Kf2 Bc4 32. h4 h5 33. Ke3 Ke7 34.
Ke4 g6 35. Nc2 Kd6 36. Ne3 Bb5) 28... Bc7 (28... Bg5 {We keep the bishop pair
no matter what.}) 29. Be5 Bxe5 30. Nxe5 Bb5 31. f4 Kf8 32. Kf2 Ke7 33. Ke3 Ke6
34. g3 f6 35. Nf3 Kd5 36. Nd2 Bd7 37. h4 Bf5 38. Nb3 Kc4 39. Nc5) (26... Ba4
27. Nd4 a6 28. Nf5 f6) 27. bxa5 Bxa5 28. Nd4 Bg6 29. Nc6 Bb6 30. Ne7+ Kh7 31.
Nxg6 Kxg6 1/2-1/2

